# Legacy redirects — earlier copies of the marketing site linked to the
# architecture page under obfuscated paths (`/claw/internal-ref-7f3a9` and
# `/claw/how-it-works`). The site now links to `/architecture/` directly;
# these redirects stay so anyone who bookmarked or shared the old URLs
# still lands on the right page. With + without the `.html` suffix
# because Netlify's pretty-URL rewriter doesn't always normalise.
/claw/internal-ref-7f3a9       /architecture/  301
/claw/internal-ref-7f3a9.html  /architecture/  301
/claw/how-it-works             /architecture/  301
/claw/how-it-works.html        /architecture/  301

# Embedded demo SPA — hash router lives under /demo/. We use 200
# REWRITES (not 301 redirects) so the URL doesn't change, and so
# there's zero risk of Netlify's trailing-slash normaliser fighting
# a 301 force and producing a "too many redirects" loop in Safari.
# Both /demo and /demo/<anything> internally serve /demo/index.html;
# the SPA's hash router takes over once it boots.
/demo        /demo/index.html  200
/demo/*      /demo/index.html  200
